{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1720,"text":"Music is the most universal\nlanguage that we have,"},{"time":5959,"text":"way more so than any dialect or tongue."},{"time":9802,"text":"You can play a melody to a child in China"},{"time":12670,"text":"and the same melody\nto a child in South Africa."},{"time":16072,"text":"And despite the huge differences\nbetween those two children,"},{"time":19728,"text":"they will still draw some of the same\ntruths from that melody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24739,"text":"Now, I think the reason why\nmusic has this universality,"},{"time":28391,"text":"this way of speaking\nto each and every one of us,"},{"time":31641,"text":"is that somehow it's capable\nof holding up a mirror to us"},{"time":35659,"text":"that reveals, in some small or large way,"},{"time":38990,"text":"a little bit of who or what we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43967,"text":"By logical extension of this,"},{"time":45760,"text":"if music is this universal force,"},{"time":48406,"text":"then surely groups of musicians --\nlet's call them orchestras --"},{"time":52350,"text":"should reflect every aspect\nof the community."},{"time":56893,"text":"Logical, but not necessarily true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60293,"text":"At TEDxBrussels today, we've been looking\nforward to the future --"},{"time":63743,"text":"50 years from now."},{"time":64918,"text":"Well, I'm going to ask you\nto go in the other direction for a minute,"},{"time":68261,"text":"to come back with me\n50 years into the past,"},{"time":70428,"text":"the early 1960s to be precise."},{"time":72573,"text":"And if you took a look\nat all the great orchestras"},{"time":75071,"text":"of the world at that time, a snapshot,"},{"time":77839,"text":"how many women do you think you would find"},{"time":80277,"text":"playing in those orchestras?"},{"time":82956,"text":"The answer: virtually none."},{"time":86356,"text":"Well, here we are 50 years on, in 2011,"},{"time":90079,"text":"and pretty much\nevery orchestra on the planet"},{"time":92256,"text":"has a fantastic and healthy balance\nbetween the sexes."},{"time":95960,"text":"\"Of course!\" I hear you\nsay, \"Totally logical.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":100652,"text":"But how about another aspect\nof the community?"},{"time":103093,"text":"The disabled community."},{"time":105189,"text":"Do we find them well-represented\nin the great orchestras of our world?"},{"time":110723,"text":"Well, I can tell you as a conductor,"},{"time":112739,"text":"I work with orchestras\naround the world all the time,"},{"time":115743,"text":"and I can count on the fingers of one hand"},{"time":119111,"text":"the number of disabled\nmusicians I've encountered"},{"time":121459,"text":"in any orchestra,"},{"time":123049,"text":"anywhere."},{"time":125008,"text":"Why is this?"},{"time":126837,"text":"You can't tell me that there\naren't millions upon millions"},{"time":130535,"text":"of prodigiously gifted musicians\nof disability around the world."},{"time":137110,"text":"Where is their platform?"},{"time":138639,"text":"Where is the infrastructure\nthat creates a space for them"},{"time":142242,"text":"so that they can collaborate\nwith other great musicians?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147227,"text":"So, ladies and gentlemen,\nas you can probably tell,"},{"time":149649,"text":"I'm on a bit of a mission."},{"time":150916,"text":"And this mission has\na personal root to it."},{"time":152991,"text":"I have four children, the youngest of whom\nwas born with cerebral palsy."},{"time":156484,"text":"She's now five, and through\nher glorious existence,"},{"time":159907,"text":"I suppose I have now become\na fully paid-up member"},{"time":163409,"text":"of the amazing, dizzyingly wonderful\ndisabled community."},{"time":168398,"text":"And I find myself looking\nat the Paralympics"},{"time":170539,"text":"and thinking what\nan incredible model that is."},{"time":173568,"text":"It's taken a good five decades, actually,"},{"time":176451,"text":"but I can say with hand on heart"},{"time":178090,"text":"that when the Paralympics\ncomes to London next year,"},{"time":180646,"text":"there will not be an intelligent\nperson anywhere on the planet"},{"time":185054,"text":"who does not absolutely believe\nin the validity of disabled sportspeople."},{"time":191066,"text":"What an amazing position to be in!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193421,"text":"So, ladies and gentlemen,\nwhere the hell is music in all this?"},{"time":197297,"text":"Apologies to any of you\nwho are sports fans,"},{"time":199844,"text":"but music is far more\nuniversal than sport."},{"time":203336,"text":"Where is the platform?\nWhere is their voice?"},{"time":206745,"text":"So, we in the UK are at the very early\nstages in forming what will be"},{"time":211801,"text":"Britain's first-ever\nnational disabled orchestra."},{"time":215572,"text":"We are going to call it\nthe British Paraorchestra,"},{"time":217930,"text":"because with the world's eyes\non London next year"},{"time":220844,"text":"and particularly on the Paralympics,"},{"time":222855,"text":"we want to throw down the gauntlet"},{"time":224556,"text":"to every single other country\nthat is represented there,"},{"time":227981,"text":"to say to them, \"Here's our paraorchestra."},{"time":230906,"text":"Where's yours?\""},{"time":232421,"text":"Every country should have\na multiplicity of paraorchestras"},{"time":236078,"text":"of all shapes and sizes,"},{"time":238123,"text":"no question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239616,"text":"Now, today is a very special day for me,"},{"time":242124,"text":"because it is the first time\nthat the first four members"},{"time":245741,"text":"of my little embryonic paraorchestra"},{"time":248550,"text":"are going to play in public;"},{"time":250711,"text":"four extraordinary musicians\nof which the number will grow and grow."},{"time":255133,"text":"I hope in the end the Paraorchestra\ncould even be as big as 50 musicians."},{"time":259705,"text":"We present to you today\na little sonic adventure,"},{"time":262764,"text":"a little piece of improvisational\nwhimsy, if you like,"},{"time":266879,"text":"a piece on which, of course,\nthe ink is still wet,"},{"time":269573,"text":"the clay is still wet."},{"time":270924,"text":"After all, improvisation\nis never a fixed thing."},{"time":273310,"text":"We decided what we wanted\nto share with you,"},{"time":275511,"text":"at the heart of our improvisation,"},{"time":277269,"text":"was a tune which is beloved\nof British people."},{"time":280156,"text":"It's one of the only folk melodies"},{"time":282004,"text":"that we still recognize in our culture."},{"time":284865,"text":"And here's an interesting thing:\nfolk music can tell you an awful lot"},{"time":288176,"text":"about the cultural DNA of the country\nfrom which it originates."},{"time":292381,"text":"You see, we in Britain\nare quietly melancholic."},{"time":296166,"text":"You know, the rain ... it does rain."},{"time":298470,"text":"The food's not so good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299822,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":300825,"text":"Quietly melancholic."},{"time":302941,"text":"Not blackly so, just quietly so."},{"time":305895,"text":"And as Shakespeare put it so\nbrilliantly in \"Twelfth Night,\""},{"time":309476,"text":"he loves music that has \"a dying fall.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":313167,"text":"So this melody, \"Greensleeves,\"\nis chock-full of \"dying fall.\""},{"time":317885,"text":"You may know this tune."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319071,"text":"(Singing) Da, da, da da da da, dying fall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321839,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":322948,"text":"Da da da, da da da da, dying fall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325485,"text":"Da dee, da da na na ... dying fall ...\nna na nee, na ah ah ah ah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328945,"text":"Brief burst of sunshine, ladies\nand gentlemen, the chorus --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":331918,"text":"(Singing) Ya da da da, dying fall ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334325,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335384,"text":"(Singing) Da da dee,\nda da da da, dying fall ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337723,"text":"Ya da da da, dying fall ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341139,"text":"OK?"},{"time":342327,"text":"It's like we need some melodic Viagra\nin our culture, ladies and gentlemen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346067,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":348376,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354375,"text":"It goes without saying"},{"time":355563,"text":"that we are very much\nat the starting gates with this project."},{"time":358536,"text":"We need your help, we need\nthe global community"},{"time":361185,"text":"to help us deliver this dream,"},{"time":363385,"text":"so that this orchestra\ncan be full steam ahead"},{"time":366937,"text":"by summer 2012."},{"time":368933,"text":"If you think there's any way \nthat you can help us,"},{"time":371389,"text":"please, please, get in touch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373794,"text":"And so, ladies and gentlemen, it gives\nme enormous pride, pleasure and joy"},{"time":378031,"text":"to introduce to you,\nwith a short improvisation"},{"time":380276,"text":"upon that most melancholic\ntune, \"Greensleeves,\""},{"time":383407,"text":"the first four members\nof the British Paraorchestra."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387932,"text":"(Applause) (Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399006,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":772209,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":781945,"text":"(Cheers) (Applause)"}]}]}